# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

Bootstrap project generated by `ai-new` on {{GENERATED_DATE}}.

## What was created

- `image/Containerfile` — the durable container image definition
- `profile.env` — profile configuration for `ai-launch` / `ai-build`
- `launchers/{{PROJECT_SLUG}}` — launch the project container
- `launchers/build-{{PROJECT_SLUG}}.sh` — build/rebuild the image
- `.env.example` — template for runtime secrets (copy to `.env`, do not commit)
- `workspace/` — host-mounted working directory

## Quick start

### 1. Review the generated files

```bash
cat image/Containerfile
cat profile.env
```

### 2. Build the image

```bash
./launchers/build-{{PROJECT_SLUG}}.sh
# or: podman build -f image/Containerfile -t localhost/{{PROJECT_SLUG}}:latest image/
```

### 3. Set up runtime secrets (if any)

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env and fill in real values — this file is gitignored
```

### 4. Launch the container

```bash
./launchers/{{PROJECT_SLUG}}
# or: ai-launch {{PROJECT_NAME}}
```

## Session notes

Bootstrap session details are in `bootstrap/session.md`.
Resume an incomplete session with: `ai-new {{PROJECT_NAME}} --resume`

## Updating the image

After modifying `image/Containerfile`, rebuild with:

```bash
./launchers/build-{{PROJECT_SLUG}}.sh
```

Then recreate the container:

```bash
ai-launch {{PROJECT_NAME}} --recreate
```
